pull_request.title: Don't use cycle count register on Raspberry Pi
Fixing BIKE compilation with GCC-6
pull_request.body:
Fix for: https://circleci.com/gh/open-quantum-safe/liboqs/3420

On GCC-6 The AVX512 intrinsic `out = _mm512_slli_epi64(a, count)` is translated to the assembly instruction `vpsllq` that expects the immediate value (count) to be a constant. In contrast, the AVX512 intrinsic `out = _mm512_sllv_epi64(a, count)` is translated to the assembly instruction `vpsllvq` that expects count to be a 512-bit variable.
When count is not a constant (as in BIKE) GCC-6 outputs an error message 
> error: the last argument must be an 8-bit immediate

while GCC-7 and above automatically translate `_mm512_slli_epi64` to `_mm512_sllv_epi64`.

In this PR I manually replaced `_mm512_slli_epi64` with `_mm512_sllv_epi64` to fix the compilation on GCC-6.
